Utterance: Hi, it's Ellie again. I'm glad to see you back today. How have you been since our last session?
Hi! I've been doing pretty well, actually. The job is going well, and I've been feeling more positive.
That's great to hear! Last time, you mentioned feeling a lot of pressure when you were unemployed. How has that changed for you?
It’s like a weight has been lifted off my shoulders. I feel more motivated now. I actually enjoy going to work every day.
That’s wonderful! Have you noticed any changes in your mood or energy levels since starting the job?
Yes, definitely! I feel more energetic and engaged. I think having a routine helps a lot.
Routines can be very beneficial. Have you been able to maintain any self-care practices in your routine?
I try to make time for reading and going to the beach, which I find really calming.
That sounds lovely. What kind of things do you read?
Mostly fiction, but I also enjoy psychology-related books. They help me understand myself better.
That’s insightful. You mentioned in our last session that you believe you struggle with depression. Have you had any thoughts about that recently?
I have. I still think about it, but I feel like I'm managing it better now. The job has really helped.
That’s a positive shift. Have you noticed any triggers that might still affect your mood?
Sometimes when I’m alone for too long, I start to feel down again. It's like I need to be around people to stay positive.
That’s a valuable insight. Have you been able to connect with friends or colleagues since starting your job?
Yes! I’ve been trying to make plans with co-workers after work, and it helps a lot.
That’s fantastic! Social connections can be very grounding. Have you felt any anxiety about making those connections?
A little, but I remind myself that everyone is just trying to get to know each other. It helps me relax.
That’s a great strategy! It seems like you’re applying some of the coping techniques we discussed last time.
Yeah, I think so! I’ve been trying to be more mindful about my feelings and not let them overwhelm me.
Mindfulness is a powerful tool. Have you practiced any specific mindfulness exercises?
I’ve been doing some breathing exercises when I feel anxious, and it really helps me focus.
Excellent! Breathing exercises can be very effective. How do you feel after practicing them?
I feel calmer and more centered. It’s like I can think more clearly.
That’s wonderful progress. Have you noticed any changes in how you react to stressors at work?
I’ve been handling stress better. I try to take a step back and breathe before reacting.
That’s a significant improvement! It sounds like you’re developing a healthier response to stress.
I think so! I feel more in control of my emotions now.
That’s a great feeling to have. Is there anything specific you would like to work on in our next session?
I think I’d like to explore how to maintain this positivity, even when I face challenges.
Absolutely, that sounds like a good goal. We can also discuss ways to strengthen your social connections.
Yes, that would be helpful! I want to keep building those relationships.
Great! I look forward to exploring that with you. Is there anything else you’d like to share before we wrap up today?
Just that I appreciate this space to talk about everything. It really helps!
I’m glad to hear that! Thank you for being open today. I look forward to our next session.
Me too! Thank you, Ellie.
Goodbye for now!
Bye!
